Connect to server

1.Use nc chall.lac.tf 31181 or Python socket.

     Solve PoW

2.Run redpwnpow with given suffix.

Send solution back.

3.Get RSA values

Receive:

n

c

e (usually 65537)

Save them.

4.Understand p structure

p = (67×'6') || (67 unknown digits: 6/7) || (67×'7')

~66% of p known → RSA broken.

5.Build polynomial

Let x = unknown middle part

p = high + x*10^67 + low

Polynomial: f(x) = high + x*10^67 + low ≡ 0 (mod n)

6.Run Coppersmith

Use SageMath

small_roots() on f(x) with proper bounds.

7.Recover p

Plug found x → full p.
8.
Compute q

q = n // p
9.
Recover private key

φ = (p-1)(q-1)

d = inverse(e, φ)
10.
Decrypt

m = pow(c, d, n)

Convert to bytes → flag.